<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>If the nominal interest rate is 7% and the inflation rate is 3%, what is the real interest rate?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">10%</option>
            <option letter="b">4%</option>
            <option letter="c">21%</option>
            <option letter="d">2.33%</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The real interest rate is calculated by subtracting the inflation rate from the nominal interest rate. In this case, 7% - 3% = 4%. This represents the actual return on investment after accounting for inflation's erosion of purchasing power.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
